	<div class="cell large-8 small-12 main-content-well">
		<div class="story-content">
							<div class="story-info">
			<div class="featured-img-container">
			<img class="story-img" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/herculinehead-726x400.jpg" title="The 11 Best Book Covers of October">
					</div>
		<div class="story-heads">
		<h1>The 11 Best Book Covers of October</h1>
		<h2>Plus a Couple Extra</h2>	</div>
	</div>
										<div class="byline-date">
					<span class="byline"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/emily-temple/"  title="Emily Temple">Emily Temple</a></span>
					<span class="hr"></span>
					<span class="date">October 30, 2025</span>
				</div>
						<div class="story-body">
								<p>Another month of books, another month of book covers: October was big, bold, and weird as all get out. I also threw in a couple of covers that I forgot in September but just couldn&#8217;t let go of&#8230;</p><div class="insert-post-ads" style="clear:both;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><span>Article continues after advertisement</span><!-- Code from Primis: LitHub_static_to_float -->
<!-- Do not serve inside a SafeFrame -->
<script type="text/javascript" language="javascript" src="https://live.primis.tech/live/liveView.php?s=120997&schain=1.0,1!publift.com,01K5AHM87E14YH1C83WXZ8HCHJ,1&cbuster=%%CACHEBUSTER%%"></script>
<!-- End of code from Primis --></div>
<span class="caption"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260344" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lily-king-on-campus-novels-time-jumps-and-having-fun-while-writing/heartthelover_hc/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/HearttheLover_HC.png" data-orig-size="1600,2440" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="HearttheLover_HC" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Lily King, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802165176&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Heart the Lover&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover art by Amanda Hudson (Grove Press, September 30)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/HearttheLover_HC-197x300.png" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/HearttheLover_HC-671x1024.png" class="wp-image-260344 size-full" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/HearttheLover_HC.png" alt="" width="1600" height="2440" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/HearttheLover_HC.png 1600w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/HearttheLover_HC-197x300.png 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/HearttheLover_HC-671x1024.png 671w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/HearttheLover_HC-768x1171.png 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/HearttheLover_HC-39x60.png 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/HearttheLover_HC-1007x1536.png 1007w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/HearttheLover_HC-1343x2048.png 1343w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/HearttheLover_HC-33x50.png 33w" sizes="(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px" /> Lily King, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780802165176" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Heart the Lover</a></em>; cover art by Amanda Hudson (Grove Press, September 30)</span>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Striking, evocative, and perfect for the book. I&#8217;ve never liked orange so much in my life.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260025" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-cartographer-of-absences/attachment/9780374616328/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780374616328.jpg" data-orig-size="1650,2531" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="cartographer of absences" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Mia Couto, tr. David Brookshaw, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374616311&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Cartographer of Absences&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Thomas Colligan (FSG, September 30)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780374616328-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780374616328-668x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-260025" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780374616328.jpg" alt="cartographer of absences" width="1650" height="2531" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780374616328.jpg 1650w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780374616328-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780374616328-668x1024.jpg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780374616328-768x1178.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780374616328-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780374616328-1001x1536.jpg 1001w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780374616328-1335x2048.jpg 1335w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/9780374616328-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="(max-width: 1650px) 100vw, 1650px" /> Mia Couto, tr. David Brookshaw, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780374616311" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Cartographer of Absences</em></a>; cover design by Thomas Colligan (FSG, September 30)</span>
<p>Just beautiful.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="261885" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-11-best-book-covers-of-october-2/version-1-0-0-60/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/51GIX1xLX3L._SL1096_.jpg" data-orig-size="685,1096" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Version 1.0.0&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="artifact" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Julija Sukys, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781959000587&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Artifact&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Kimberly Glyder (West University Press, October 1)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/51GIX1xLX3L._SL1096_-188x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/51GIX1xLX3L._SL1096_-640x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-261885" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/51GIX1xLX3L._SL1096_.jpg" alt="artifact" width="685" height="1096" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/51GIX1xLX3L._SL1096_.jpg 685w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/51GIX1xLX3L._SL1096_-188x300.jpg 188w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/51GIX1xLX3L._SL1096_-640x1024.jpg 640w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/51GIX1xLX3L._SL1096_-38x60.jpg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/51GIX1xLX3L._SL1096_-31x50.jpg 31w" sizes="(max-width: 685px) 100vw, 685px" /> Julija Sukys, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781959000587" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Artifact</em></a>; cover design by Kimberly Glyder (West University Press, October 1)</span>
<p>That meticulous hand-cutting! You have to marvel at it.</p><div class="insert-post-ads" style="clear:both;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><span>Article continues after advertisement</span><!-- GAM 22020028882/LTHB_lithubcom/Article_Incontent_1 -->
<div data-fuse="Article_Incontent_1"></div></div>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255929" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/9781646222537-copy/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9781646222537-copy.jpg" data-orig-size="662,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="Brenda Lozano, tr. Heather Cleary, Mothers" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Brenda Lozano, tr. Heather Cleary, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646222537&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Mothers&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Jaya Miceli (Catapult, October 7)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9781646222537-copy-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9781646222537-copy.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-255929" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9781646222537-copy.jpg" alt="Brenda Lozano, tr. Heather Cleary, Mothers" width="662" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9781646222537-copy.jpg 662w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9781646222537-copy-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9781646222537-copy-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/9781646222537-copy-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="(max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px" /> Brenda Lozano, tr. Heather Cleary, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781646222537" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Mothers</em></a>; cover design by Jaya Miceli (Catapult, October 7)</span>
<p>Deranged, in a good way.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="261886" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-11-best-book-covers-of-october-2/a11bq26au1l-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/A11BQ26Au1L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="667,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="the mind reels" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Fredrik DeBoer, &lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781566897372&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Mind Reels&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Kyle Hunter (Coffee House Press, October 7)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/A11BQ26Au1L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/A11BQ26Au1L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-261886" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/A11BQ26Au1L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="the mind reels" width="667" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/A11BQ26Au1L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 667w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/A11BQ26Au1L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/A11BQ26Au1L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/A11BQ26Au1L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="(max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px" /> Fredrik DeBoer, <a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781566897372" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>The Mind Reels</em></a>; cover design by Kyle Hunter (Coffee House Press, October 7)</span>
<p>The placement of the numbers over the eyes gives this cover a gleeful weirdness that is woefully rare these days.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255933" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/herculine-9781668087862_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/herculine-9781668087862_hr.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2146" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Grace Byron, Herculine" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Grace Byron, &lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668087862&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Herculine&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Ella Laytham; illustration by Evangeline Gallagher (S&amp;amp;S/Saga Press, October 7)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/herculine-9781668087862_hr-196x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/herculine-9781668087862_hr-668x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-255933" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/herculine-9781668087862_hr.jpg" alt="Grace Byron, Herculine" width="1400" height="2146" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/herculine-9781668087862_hr.jpg 1400w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/herculine-9781668087862_hr-196x300.jpg 196w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/herculine-9781668087862_hr-668x1024.jpg 668w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/herculine-9781668087862_hr-768x1177.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/herculine-9781668087862_hr-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/herculine-9781668087862_hr-1002x1536.jpg 1002w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/herculine-9781668087862_hr-1336x2048.jpg 1336w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/herculine-9781668087862_hr-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px" /> Grace Byron, <a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668087862" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Herculine</em></a>; cover design by Ella Laytham; illustration by Evangeline Gallagher (S&amp;S/Saga Press, October 7)</span>
<p>Color, pattern, image, style—and I love the way the title bleeds.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="261887" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-11-best-book-covers-of-october-2/81kdxhen7wl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81KDXHen7WL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="648,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="unfit" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Ariana Harwicz, tr. Jessie Mendez Sayer, &lt;em&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238892&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;Unfit&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;; cover design by Erik Carter (New Directions, October 14)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81KDXHen7WL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-194x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81KDXHen7WL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-261887" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81KDXHen7WL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" alt="unfit" width="648" height="1000" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81KDXHen7WL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 648w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81KDXHen7WL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-194x300.jpg 194w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81KDXHen7WL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/81KDXHen7WL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-32x50.jpg 32w" sizes="(max-width: 648px) 100vw, 648px" /> Ariana Harwicz, tr. Jessie Mendez Sayer, <em><a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780811238892" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external">Unfit</a></em>; cover design by Erik Carter (New Directions, October 14)</span>
<p>So simple, so brilliant.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260669" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/happy-bad/attachment/9781662603280/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280.jpg" data-orig-size="800,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="happy bad" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Delaney Nolan, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662603280&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Happy Bad&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Adriana Tonello and Rodrigo Corral (Astra House, October 14)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-683x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-260669" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280.jpg" alt="happy bad" width="800" height="1200" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280.jpg 800w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603280-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /> Delaney Nolan, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662603280" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Happy Bad</em></a>; cover design by Adriana Tonello and Rodrigo Corral (Astra House, October 14)</span>
<p>I love the inverted As.</p><div class="insert-post-ads" style="clear:both;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><span>Article continues after advertisement</span><!-- GAM 22020028882/LTHB_lithubcom/Article_Incontent_2 -->
<div data-fuse="Article_Incontent_2"></div></div>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="260667" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/minor-black-figures/minor-black-figures-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures.jpg" data-orig-size="795,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="minor black figures" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Brandon Taylor, &lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593332368&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Minor Black Figures&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Grace Han (Riverhead, October 14)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-199x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-678x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-260667" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures.jpg" alt="" width="795" height="1200" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures.jpg 795w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-768x1159.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/minor-black-figures-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="(max-width: 795px) 100vw, 795px" /> Brandon Taylor, <a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9780593332368" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Minor Black Figures</em></a>; cover design by Grace Han (Riverhead, October 14)</span>
<p>The depth Han creates here with just the text is masterful.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255953" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/81qsahg-h5l-_sl1500_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81Qsahg-h5L._SL1500_.jpg" data-orig-size="1045,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Michelle Tea, Little F" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Michelle Tea, &lt;a class=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781558613560&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Little F&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Tree Abraham (Feminist Press, October 14)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81Qsahg-h5L._SL1500_-209x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81Qsahg-h5L._SL1500_-713x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-255953" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81Qsahg-h5L._SL1500_.jpg" alt="Michelle Tea, Little F" width="1045" height="1500" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81Qsahg-h5L._SL1500_.jpg 1045w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81Qsahg-h5L._SL1500_-209x300.jpg 209w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81Qsahg-h5L._SL1500_-713x1024.jpg 713w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81Qsahg-h5L._SL1500_-768x1102.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81Qsahg-h5L._SL1500_-42x60.jpg 42w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/81Qsahg-h5L._SL1500_-35x50.jpg 35w" sizes="(max-width: 1045px) 100vw, 1045px" /> Michelle Tea, <a class="external" href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781558613560" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Little F</em></a>; cover design by Tree Abraham (Feminist Press, October 14)</span>
<p>One of the best signage covers I&#8217;ve seen in a while.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="255964" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2025-part-two/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2100" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Erin Somers, The Ten Year Affair" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Erin Somers, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668081440&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Ten Year Affair&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Emily Mahon; cover art by Shannon Cartier Lucy (Simon &amp;amp; Schuster, October 21)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-683x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-255964" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr.jpg" alt="Erin Somers, The Ten Year Affair" width="1400" height="2100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr.jpg 1400w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/the-ten-year-affair-9781668081440_hr-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px" /> Erin Somers, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781668081440" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>The Ten Year Affair</em></a>; cover design by Emily Mahon; cover art by Shannon Cartier Lucy (Simon &amp; Schuster, October 21)</span>
<p>A great choice of art married (haha) to the perfect text treatment.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="261889" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-11-best-book-covers-of-october-2/attachment/9781662602962/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662602962-scaled.jpg" data-orig-size="1707,2560" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="look out" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Edward McPherson, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602955&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Look Out&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Arsh Raziuddin (Astra House, October 21)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662602962-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662602962-683x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-261889" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662602962-scaled.jpg" alt="look out" width="1707" height="2560" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662602962-scaled.jpg 1707w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662602962-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662602962-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662602962-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662602962-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662602962-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662602962-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662602962-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="(max-width: 1707px) 100vw, 1707px" /> Edward McPherson, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662602955" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Look Out</em></a>; cover design by Arsh Raziuddin (Astra House, October 21)</span>
<p>There&#8217;s so much going on here, I don&#8217;t even know where to look—I find this oddly refreshing.</p>
<span class="caption"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="261890" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/the-11-best-book-covers-of-october-2/9781662603044-2/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603044.jpg" data-orig-size="800,1200" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="i deliver parcels in beijing" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="&lt;p&gt;Hu Anyan, tr. Jack Hargreaves, &lt;a href=&quot;https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662603044&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;I Deliver Parcels in Beijing&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; cover design by Rodrigo Corral; illustration by Klaus Kremmerz (Astra House, October 28)&lt;/p&gt;
" data-medium-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603044-200x300.jpg" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603044-683x1024.jpg" class="size-full wp-image-261890" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603044.jpg" alt="i deliver parcels in beijing" width="800" height="1200" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603044.jpg 800w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603044-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603044-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603044-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603044-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/9781662603044-33x50.jpg 33w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /> Hu Anyan, tr. Jack Hargreaves, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/132/9781662603044" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>I Deliver Parcels in Beijing</em></a>; cover design by Rodrigo Corral; illustration by Klaus Kremmerz (Astra House, October 28)</span>
<p>All about the illustration here.</p><div class="insert-post-ads" style="clear:both;width:100%;margin:0 0 20px 0;"><span>Article continues after advertisement</span><!-- GAM 22020028882/LTHB_lithubcom/Article_Incontent_3 -->
